		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_CANDY_FACTORY_HELP">
			<Text>+ 1 [ICON_RES_CANDY] Candy luxury. Each source of [ICON_RES_SUGAR] Suagr and [ICON_RES_COCOA] Cocoa worked by this City produces +1 [ICON_GOLD] Gold. Improved trade route [ICON_GOLD] income to and from this City. No more than 3 may be built.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_CANDY_FACTORY_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Candy Factory is an Industrial era building which grants 1 source of [ICON_RES_CANDY] Candy and increases a City's [ICON_GOLD] Gold income from [ICON_RES_SUGAR] Suagr and [ICON_RES_COCOA] Cocoa and trade. It requires an improved source of either near your City to be built. No more than 3 may be built.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_CANDY_FACTORY_PEDIA">
			<Text>The candy business underwent a drastic change in the 1830s when technological advances and the availability of sugar opened up the market. The new market was not only for the enjoyment of the rich but also for the pleasure of the working class as well. There was also an increasing market for children. While some fine confectioners remained, the candy store became a staple of the child of the Western working class. Penny candies epitomized this transformation of candy.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]--Wikipedia</Text>
		</Row>
